snippet.title: UFC 296 RECAP: Tony Ferguson vs Paddy Pimblett Full Fight Highlight Video
snippet.description:
Paddy Pimblett's triumph over Tony Ferguson at UFC 296 unfolded as a captivating 15-minute spectacle, culminating in a decisive unanimous decision victory. Despite initial aspirations for an early finish, Pimblett's performance demonstrated a profound level of control and skill throughout the bout, leaving an indelible mark on the T-Mobile Arena. #UFC296 #tonyferguson #paddypimblett 

Hailing from Liverpool, Pimblett showcased his striking prowess in the first round, where Ferguson resiliently weathered a barrage of attacks. The relentless pressure applied by Pimblett eventually resulted in a dramatic knockdown, prompting an eager pursuit of a finish on the canvas. Despite Ferguson's tenacious defensive maneuvers, Pimblett maintained unwavering control, showcasing a masterful display of ground-and-pound expertise.

As the fight progressed, Pimblett continued to assert his dominance on the ground, effectively fending off Ferguson's attempts from the bottom. Even as signs of fatigue surfaced in the third round, Pimblett executed yet another well-timed takedown, securing the win with a calculated flurry of punches.

With all three judges unanimously scoring the contest 30-27 in favor of Pimblett, he celebrated the hard-earned victory while acknowledging Ferguson's undeniable toughness. The match not only highlighted Pimblett's growth as he moved to an impressive 21-3 in his career but also raised questions about Ferguson's future in the sport as he faced his seventh consecutive defeat.

Click here to Subscribe to our YouTube channel http://bit.ly/2quZwsz

Follow My Twitter https://twitter.com/Keanutalksmma

Click here to like our Facebook page 
https://bit.ly/2ZmykdU

Watch our most recent video!

The electrifying atmosphere at T-Mobile Arena, characterized by the contrasting walkout songs and a divided crowd, added an extra layer of intensity to the lightweight bout. Pimblett's triumphant return to the Octagon after a year-long hiatus due to injuries underscored his resilience and marked a compelling comeback story. Meanwhile, Ferguson's struggles, despite his collaboration with fitness motivator David Goggins, raised further speculation about the trajectory of his career.

In the aftermath of the bout, Pimblett's victory stood as a testament to his evolving skill set and strategic prowess. The Liverpool native's calculated approach, coupled with his striking performance, showcased a fighter in the prime of his career. As Pimblett celebrated, the echoes of his triumphant return resonated not only within the arena but across the broader landscape of the MMA world.

More about Parking Tycoon (from Steam):

ABOUT THIS GAME
Ready to dive into the exciting world of car parking management? Take charge and become the ultimate Parking Lot Tycoon in this thrilling first-person simulation game! Get behind the wheel and drive your success to new heights.

Unleash Your Business Acumen
As a first-person simulation game, "Parking Lot Tycoon" puts you in the driver's seat of a car parking manager. You own a vast expanse of land, ready to be transformed into a profitable parking empire. Your objective is simple but challenging: build and manage parking lots to maximize your revenue and establish yourself as the top tycoon in the industry.

Strategic Planning and Upgrades
Every decision counts in your quest for success. Strategically develop and upgrade your parking facilities, ensuring they are attractive, secure, and equipped with the latest technology. Expand your empire by acquiring new properties, optimizing space utilization, and providing exceptional customer service. The sky's the limit!

Uncover an Engaging Story
Beyond the exciting gameplay, "Parking Lot Tycoon" delivers an intriguing narrative experience. Unravel the mysteries of the land you own as you progress through the game. Discover the history behind its affordability and uncover the truth behind the legendary curse that has haunted previous owners. Cutscenes triggered by milestones will immerse you in a captivating storyline, adding depth and excitement to your entrepreneurial journey.

Face Challenges Head-On
Building a parking empire is not without its obstacles. Prepare to tackle unforeseen setbacks and overcome them with your wit and ingenuity. As you develop the land, you may encounter equipment malfunctions, unexplained accidents, or strange weather phenomena. Don't let these challenges deter you! Find innovative solutions, debunk superstitions, and turn setbacks into opportunities.

Master the Art of Revenue Maximization
Your success as a Parking Lot Tycoon hinges on your ability to keep your hourly rates competitive and attract a steady stream of customers. Balance pricing strategies with customer satisfaction to create a thriving business. Prevent criminal activities, maintain the safety of parked vehicles, and provide exceptional service to keep customers coming back for more.

üöóüíº Are you ready to build your parking empire and rewrite the history of the land? Embark now on an exhilarating journey of entrepreneurship. Your destiny as the ultimate Parking Lot Tycoon awaits! üÖøÔ∏è

snippet.title: Biggest Argument Settled! (boat build update)
snippet.description:
Our HH44 CURIOSITY is getting so close to being complete we can taste the salt on our lips.¬† ‚ù§ Join Our Crew!  ‚ù§ For exclusive content, behind the scenes & Q&A's:

 - https://bit.ly/motion-array-GWTW 

üéΩGET YOUR SWAG ON:  https://gonewiththewynns.teemill.com/

üíØFREE ways to support our productions
http://bit.ly/join-gwtw

_________________________________________

It‚Äôs been a big week here at the HH Catamarans factory filled with completed installations and even a little time out on the water.¬† Our HH44 CURIOSITY is getting so close to being complete we can taste the salt on our lips.¬† Mast is stepped, propellers are fitted, copper bottom paint is on and the dinghy is commissioned. Now all we need is some sails and we are ready to get wet.¬†¬†

Plus, we reveal the completed installation of what has no doubt been the most debated piece of equipment of this entire boat building saga.

Never in my wildest dreams did I think building a new boat would be this much work.¬† And we‚Äôre not even the ones doing the labor.¬†

Our days and nights are filled to the brim with decisions to be made, parts to be purchased and logistics to be planned (oh how I have NOT missed maritime bureaucracy).¬† The closer handover day gets, the more complicated the logistics seem to get.¬† Boat insurance for SE Asia looks expensive and potentially difficult to obtain.¬† We‚Äôre still searching for the port of least resistance to check into the Philippines and sailing out of China, well that is a whole other kettle of fish.¬†

So many adventures ahead with so many variables to plan for.¬† We have gained a boat load of knowledge over the past 2 years (much more than expected) and we still have soooo much more to learn.¬† We are fortunate HH Catamarans has been so open to letting us roam free in the yard, film without abandon and ask 1001 questions.¬†

Thank you so much for being a part of this untethered journey with us. ¬†It‚Äôs been a rollercoaster of a year, and I don‚Äôt expect 2024 will be anything less.¬† So, rest up, have the most wonderful holiday break and we will see you in the new year!

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

WE‚ÄôRE JASON AND NIKKI WYNN.  A couple of modern-day documentarians, perpetual travelers, and seekers of tall tales.  

We‚Äôve been chasing our curiosity around the world on wheels and keels since 2011. Why?  Because curiosity is the key to unlocking life.  It pushes us outside our comfort zone, softens our assumptions, and helps us embrace the great unknown.  The more we let our curiosity lead the way, the more we discover about ourselves and the world around us.

Our home is also our transportation and we spend weeks away from civilization and sometimes land.  Self-reliance and living a sustainable lifestyle are a must.  It's all about managing our resources and we‚Äôre always looking for new and better ways to do so.  

We've lived off the grid for over 10 years now in everything from a Van to RV to a Sailboat. And over time we have learned a lot about renewable energy, creating safe drinking water, and managing our waste.

Our journey is ever-evolving but the mission remains the same: #CultivateCuriosity

A Definitive Ranking of 2023 Pop Culture Moments

my new years resolution is to stop bringing up snap snap 

I can't believe it's already time for this video! This time last year we definitively ranked pop culture and meme moments from 2022 and I had a few of you ask for a 2023 version so here we are. Also thanks to everyone who has been sending stuff in over the past few weeks, really appreciate it :))  also x2 sorry if i sound quieter than usual i had the flu when i was recording this go easy on meeee thank u LOL and final also... (sorry) you prob noticed i had to try a different set up for filming this one, because this was a longer list and the tier size was going to change a lot i realized the easiest way to keep as much of it in view as possible was to ditch the green screen for this one so hope you dont mind!!!  

Ok SO after consulting you guys (and myself lol) i widdled down all the pop culture moments and memes that happened this year whether they were tik tok trends, twitter moments, celebrity pop culture stuff or other noteworthy events for us to rank today! We're talking the Josh Hutcherson whistle meme, Harry Styles going bald, Taylor Swift enjoying seemingly... ranch? The Pedro Pascal renaissance on Tiktok,  the "girly teen girl" twitter debate, Lana Del Rey working at waffle house and tons of other stuff too. 

Like I mentioned in the video this list isn't exhaustive, because my tier names are the way they are there are some things that just flat out do not make sense to rank within it lol so hope that's understandable! As always with these videos though while the ranking is definitive for me it doesn't have to be for you! Feel free to share your ranking in the comments i love seeing them :)) ALSO IF ANY OF YALL HAVE SEEN THOSE MONKEYS ON TIKTOK PLEEEEEEASE TELL ME I FEEL LIKE IM GOING CRAZY NONE OF MY IRLS HAVE SEEN THEM LMAO 

And ofc!!! hope you guys have a good holiday!! This time of the year can get super hectic and stressful so hope you're taking care of yourself. this past year on the internet has been so fun with yall and i seriously cant thank u enough for it i feel like a cornball when i try to explain it but i hope you know i feel really lucky and happy to have you guys, see you in the new year :) 

ok i'll wrap it up lol if you liked the video feel free to give it like and subscribe to the channel it really helps me out :) you can also turn on my post notifications if you want to be notified every time I upload but otherwise, hope you guys enjoy and I'll see you in the comments!!

my new years resolution is to stop bringing up snap snap 

I can't believe it's already time for this video! This time last year we definitively ranked pop culture and meme moments from 2022 and I had a few of you ask for a 2023 version so here we are. Also thanks to everyone who has been sending stuff in over the past few weeks, really appreciate it :))  also x2 sorry if i sound quieter than usual i had the flu when i was recording this go easy on meeee thank u LOL and final also... (sorry) you prob noticed i had to try a different set up for filming this one, because this was a longer list and the tier size was going to change a lot i realized the easiest way to keep as much of it in view as possible was to ditch the green screen for this one so hope you dont mind!!!  

Ok SO after consulting you guys (and myself lol) i widdled down all the pop culture moments and memes that happened this year whether they were tik tok trends, twitter moments, celebrity pop culture stuff or other noteworthy events for us to rank today! We're talking the Josh Hutcherson whistle meme, Harry Styles going bald, Taylor Swift enjoying seemingly... ranch? The Pedro Pascal renaissance on Tiktok,  the "girly teen girl" twitter debate, Lana Del Rey working at waffle house and tons of other stuff too. 

Like I mentioned in the video this list isn't exhaustive, because my tier names are the way they are there are some things that just flat out do not make sense to rank within it lol so hope that's understandable! As always with these videos though while the ranking is definitive for me it doesn't have to be for you! Feel free to share your ranking in the comments i love seeing them :)) ALSO IF ANY OF YALL HAVE SEEN THOSE MONKEYS ON TIKTOK PLEEEEEEASE TELL ME I FEEL LIKE IM GOING CRAZY NONE OF MY IRLS HAVE SEEN THEM LMAO 

And ofc!!! hope you guys have a good holiday!! This time of the year can get super hectic and stressful so hope you're taking care of yourself. this past year on the internet has been so fun with yall and i seriously cant thank u enough for it i feel like a cornball when i try to explain it but i hope you know i feel really lucky and happy to have you guys, see you in the new year :) 

ok i'll wrap it up lol if you liked the video feel free to give it like and subscribe to the channel it really helps me out :) you can also turn on my post notifications if you want to be notified every time I upload but otherwise, hope you guys enjoy and I'll see you in the comments!!

snippet.title: Tiger and Charlie Woods shoot 8-under 64 | Round 1 | PNC Championship | 2023
snippet.description:
In the opening round of the 2023 PNC Championship, Tiger and Charlie Woods carded a combined 8-under 64.

SUBSCRIBE to PGA TOUR now: http://pgat.us/vBxcZSh

The PNC Championship is held for the 26th time this week as the Ritz-Carlton Golf Club in Orlando, Florida, hosts 20 two-player teams featuring a PGA Tour, Champions tour or LPGA player and one of their family members. After Tiger Woods made his return to action at the Hero World Challenge for the first time since withdrawing at the Masters, he‚Äôll once again be back to tee it up at the PNC Championship alongside his son, Charlie. The duo was tied for second a year ago after the first round, but stalled on Sunday and ended up tied for eighth. Justin Thomas returns this year to play alongside his father, Mike.  Justin Thomas finished third at the Hero World Challenge two weeks ago and will be feeling confident about taking his second PNC Championship title, as the Thomases won here in 2020. Defending champions Vijay Singh and his son Qass are looking to recreate their magic from 2022. Last year was their 16th time teeing it up together at this event, and they finally broke through for a win, becoming the first pair to shoot two sub-60 rounds at the event. Other pairings to look out for are Nelly Korda and her father Petr, Matt Kuchar and his elder son Cameron, and Bernhard Langer and his son Jason.

In this Minecraft Hermitcraft episode, I talk about the end of Hermitcraft Season 9, what the future of Hermitcraft season 10 looks like, and why Hermitcraft 9 was a bit different from other seasons for me. Reflecting on Hermitcraft season 9 has been really enjoyable, and despite it's challenges I am still really proud of what I have achieved. 

Filming channel: https://www.youtube.com/user/ThatMumboJumbo2
Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/officialmumbo/
Twitter: https://twitter.com/ThatMumboJumbo
